      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "When you feel so fundamentally empty, it can feel like the self that drives experience has vanished entirely. That sensation of being just a vessel, disconnected from your own core, is incredibly isolating and painful. It might be helpful to shift the focus from *feeling* something to simply *acknowledging* what your body is doing right now in this present moment. If this pervasive emptiness persists, connecting with a therapist who specializes in derealization or existential distress could provide a much deeper form of support.",
      "source": "target",
